		<div class="block-contributor-bio small">
			<p><strong><span class="smallcaps">Rebecca McClanahan</span></strong>&rsquo;s tenth book is <em>The Tribal Knot: A Memoir of Family, Community, and a Century of Change</em>. Recently she and her husband moved back to North Carolina after a decade in New York, where she logged hundreds of hours on Central Park benches. She teaches in the <span class="smallcaps">MFA</span> programs at Queens University of Charlotte and Rainier Writing Workshop.&nbsp;</p><a href="/contributors/rebecca-mcclanahan" class="block-contributor-link link-alt small">More From This Contributor&nbsp;&#9656;</a>		</div>
